  12+ 31C2              // interpret    --
  13+ 31C2              // This is the text interpreter.
  14+ 31C2              // It executes or compiles, depending on STATE, the text coming from
  15+ 31C2              // current input stream.
  16+ 31C2              // If the word search fails after parsing CONTEXT and CURRENT vocabulary,
  17+ 31C2              // the word is interpreted as numeric and converted, using current BASE,
  18+ 31C2              // leaving on top of stack a single or double precision number, depending
  19+ 31C2              // on the presence of a decimal point.
  20+ 31C2              // If the number conversion fails, the terminal is notified with ? followed
  21+ 31C2              // by the offending word.
