 139+ 3246              // Any new vocabulary is structured as follow:
 140+ 3246              // PFA+0 points to DOES> part of VOCABULARY to perform CELL+ CONTEXT !
 141+ 3246              // PFA+2 is 81,A0 i.e. a null-word used as LATEST in the new vocabulary
 142+ 3246              // PFA+4 always contains the LATEST word of this VOCABULARY.
 143+ 3246              //       at creations it points to the null-word of its parent vocabulary
 144+ 3246              //       that is normally FORTH, For example ASSEMBLER points FORTH's null-word
 145+ 3246              // PFA+6 is the pointer that builds up the vocabulary linked list.
 146+ 3246              //       FORTH has 0 here to signal the end of the list and user's variable
 147+ 3246              //       VOC-LINK points to PFA+6 of the newest vocabulary created.
 148+ 3246              //       While FORTH is the only vocabulary, VOC-LINK points to FORTH's PFA+6
 149+ 3246              //       When ASSEMBLER is created, its PFA+6 points to FORTH's PFA+6, and so on
 150+ 3246
